MBOMBELA – The man accused of killing Johanica Orton (34) in a hit and run, died on Sunday. Bossies Community Justice’s (BCJ) Albert Gryvenstein said Phillip Watkins (50) had passed away. “ He was ill and had diabetes. But we are awaiting confirmation on what the cause of death was. He was supposed to appear in the Nelspruit Magistrate Court on March 5.”
Johanica was killed on October 28. Watkins was arrested later that day. Read more in Tuesday’s Lowvelder.